- \(P(\text{neither}) = 0.08\)
- \(P(P) = P(C) + 0.16\)

The probability of visiting neither is \(P(\text{neither}) = 1 - P(P \text{ or } C)\), so:
\[
P(P \text{ or } C) = 1 - 0.08 = 0.92
\]

The formula for the union is:
\[
P(P \text{ or } C) = P(P) + P(C) - P(\text{both})
\]
Substituting the known values:
\[
0.92 = P(P) + P(C) - 0.28
\]
\[
