\]
Solving for \(P(C)\):
\[
0.92 + 0.12 = 2P(C)
\]
\[
1.04 = 2P(C)
\]
\[
P(C) = \frac{1.04}{2} = 0.52
\]
Now, substitute back to find \(P(P)\):
\[
P(P) = P(C) + 0.16 = 0.52 + 0.16 = 0.68
\]

