The event \(Y_7 < 27.3\) is equivalent to at least seven observations being less than 27.3. The number of observations less than 27.3 follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\). Thus, \(P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(K \geq 7)\) where \(K \sim \text{Binomial}(8, 0.7)\).

