\[
n = \left( \frac{2.326 \cdot 1.723}{0.25} \right)^2
\]

First, calculate \(2.326 \cdot 1.723 = 4.007698\).  
Then, \(4.007698 / 0.25 = 16.030792\).  
Finally, \(16.030792^2 = 256.986292\).

Since sample size must be an integer and rounding up ensures the margin of error is met, \(n = 257\).

