- Of those with an irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure, so the percentage with both irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure is 35% of 17% = 0.35 × 17 = 5.95%.  
- 65% have normal blood pressure (N), calculated as 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%.  
- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have an irregular heartbeat, so the percentage with both irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure is 11% of 65% = 0.11 × 65 = 7.15%.  

The total percentage with irregular heartbeat is the sum of those with irregular heartbeat and high, normal, or low blood pressure:  
17% = 5.95% + 7.15% + percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure (I and L).  
Solving for (I and L):  
17% - 5.95% - 7.15% = 3.90%.  

The percentage with low blood pressure includes both regular and irregular heartbeat cases:  
19% = percentage with low blood pressure and regular heartbeat (R and L) + percentage with low blood pressure and irregular heartbeat (I and L).  
Solving for (R and L):  
19% - 3.90% = 15.10%.  

Rounding to a reasonable number of significant figures (three significant figures), 15.10% becomes 15.1%.  

Thus, the percentage of patients with a regular heartbeat and low blood pressure is 15.1.

Summary: The final answer is $15.1$
