Solution: The dissociation energy from the bottom of the potential well, \( D_e \), is calculated using the formula \( D_e = D_0 + \text{ZPE} \), where ZPE is the zero-point energy. The zero-point energy is given by \( \text{ZPE} = \frac{1}{2} \omega_e - \frac{1}{4} \omega_e x_e \).

